Detailed Description

This file describes the software interface for the General Purpose Input/Output (GPIO) module.

This module contains the core GPIO pins. For a list of which pins this includes, consult the defines in this header file. Other GPIO pins exist that are not in this module, they will be available through the software interface provided by the module they belong to.

Some GPIO pins share settings for slew rate, drive strength and schmitt triggering. Consult the comments at the end of this header file for the groupings.

This API provides the facility to register pins which may be configured as input or output. The GPIO interrupt transition/level detection system can be configured and maintained.

All GPIO API callback functions are called in the interrupt context. The code for these callbacks should be short and adhere to interrupt context code execution rules defined in the MeOS documentation.

Some GPIO API functions may be called under interrupt context. Consult the individual function documentation.

Typedef Documentation

typedef void(* GPIO_CALLBACK_T)(IMG_PVOID pContext, GPIO_LEVEL_T Level)

Callback function definition. Context contains the value given at GPIOInterruptEnable, Level indicates the level on the pin that caused the interrupt.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum GPIO_STATUS_T

These define the GPIO API function return values.

Enumerator:
GPIO_STATUS_OK  Function completed normally
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_INITIALISED  Error: GPIO has already been initialised
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_UNINITIALISED  Error: GPIO has not been initialised
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_ACTIVE  Error: Pin is already active
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_ACTIVEPINS  Error: Active pins remain, cannot deinitialise
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_INACTIVE  Error: Pin is not active
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_REPEAT  Error: This pin has already been registered with the API
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_BLOCK  Error: The block index parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_PIN  Error: The pin number parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_DIRECTION  Error: The direction parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_LEVEL  Error: The level parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_PULLUP_PULLDOWN  Error: The pullup/pulldown parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_DRIVE_STRENGTH  Error: The drive strength parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_SLEW_RATE  Error: The slew rate parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_SCHMITT  Error: The schmitt parameter was not valid
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_INTERRUPT_TYPE  Error: The interrupt type parameter was not valid

enum GPIO_LEVEL_T

These define the GPIO pin logic levels.

Enumerator:
GPIO_LEVEL_LOW  Low
GPIO_LEVEL_HIGH  High

enum GPIO_DIRECTION_T

These define the GPIO pin directions.

Enumerator:
GPIO_DIR_OUTPUT  Pin is suitable for output (either High or Low).
GPIO_DIR_INPUT  Pin is high impedance, suitable for input.

enum GPIO_PULLUP_PULLDOWN_T

These define the GPIO pin output pullup/pulldown configurations.

Enumerator:
GPIO_PU_PD_OFF  Pullup/pulldown not connected (Z)
GPIO_PU_PD_PULLUP  Pullup
GPIO_PU_PD_PULLDOWN  Pulldown
GPIO_PU_PD_BUS_KEEPER  Bus keeper enabled

enum GPIO_DRIVE_STRENGTH_T

These define the GPIO pin options for drive strength

Enumerator:
GPIO_DRIVE_2MA  2mA drive strength
GPIO_DRIVE_4MA  4mA drive strength
GPIO_DRIVE_8MA  8mA drive strength
GPIO_DRIVE_16MA  16mA drive strength

enum GPIO_SCHMITT_T

These define the GPIO pin options for schmitt triggering

Enumerator:
GPIO_SCHMITT_OFF  No schmitt trigger
GPIO_SCHMITT_ON  Schmitt trigger

enum GPIO_SLEW_T

These define the GPIO pin options for slew rate

Enumerator:
GPIO_SLEW_SLOW  Slow slew rate
GPIO_SLEW_FAST  Fast slew rate

enum GPIO_INTERRUPT_TYPE_T

These define the GPIO pin interrupt configuration options.

Enumerator:
GPIO_INT_TYPE_LEVEL_LOW  Level detection - low polarity.
GPIO_INT_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH  Level detection - high polarity.
GPIO_INT_TYPE_EDGE_FALL  Edge/transition detection - falling edge.
GPIO_INT_TYPE_EDGE_RISE  Edge/transition detection - rising edge.
GPIO_INT_TYPE_EDGE_TRANSITION  Edge/transition detection - rising and falling edge.

Function Documentation

GPIO_STATUS_T GPIOInit (  ) 

Description:
This function is used to initialise the GPIO API. It should be called prior to any other GPIO API functions being called. This function should not be called in the interrupt context.

Returns:
This function returns as follows:
GPIO_STATUS_OK Operation completed successfully.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_INITIALISED Already initialised.

GPIO_STATUS_T GPIOAddPin ( GPIO_PIN_T *  psPin,
img_uint8  ui8BlockIndex,
img_uint8  ui8PinNumber,
GPIO_PIN_SETTINGS_T *  psSettings 
)

Description:
This function is used to initialise a GPIO pin. Interrupts will be initially disabled for the pin following a call to this function. The pin descriptor must be initialised prior to being used with other GPIO API functions. This function can be called in the interrupt context.

Parameters:
*psPin Pointer to pin descriptor. The bActive member must be set to IMG_FALSE. The pin descriptor must be preserved until a call is made to GPIORemovePin with the pin descriptor.
ui8BlockIndex Index of the block the pin belongs to. Consult the defines in this header file to obtain block indexes and pin numbers
ui8PinNumber Pin number within the block. Consult the defines in this header file to obtain block indexes and pin numbers
*psSettings Pointer to initial settings for the pin.
Returns:
This function returns as follows:
GPIO_STATUS_OK Operation completed successfully.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_UNINITIALISED GPIO has not been intialised.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_ACTIVE Pin descriptor is already active.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_BLOCK Invalid block index.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_PIN Invalid pin number.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_REPEAT Pin already registered with another descriptor.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_SCHMITT invalid schmitt parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_PULLUP_PULLDOWN Invalid pullup/pulldown parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_LEVEL Invalid level parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_DRIVE_STRENGTH Invalid drive strength parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_SLEW_RATE Invalid slew rate parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_DIRECTION Invalid direction parameter.

GPIO_PIN_SETTINGS_T *  psSettings

GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_PULLUP_PULLDOWN Invalid pullup/pulldown parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_LEVEL Invalid level parameter.

GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_SLEW_RATE Invalid slew rate parameter.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_DIRECTION Invalid direction parameter.

GPIO_STATUS_T GPIOSet ( GPIO_PIN_T *  psPin,
GPIO_LEVEL_T  Level 
)

Description:
This function sets the level of a GPIO line to high or low. This function should only be called for GPIO lines that have been set to I/O direction output. This function can be called in the interrupt context.

Parameters:
psPin Pointer to initialised pin descriptor.
Level The logic level to which the pin is to be set.
Returns:
This function returns as follows:
GPIO_OK Function completed normally
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_UNINITIALISED GPIO has not been intialised.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_INACTIVE Pin descriptor is inactive.
GPIO_STATUS_INVALID_LEVEL Level parameter is invalid.

Returns:

GPIO_STATUS_T GPIORemovePin ( GPIO_PIN_T *  psPin  ) 

Description:
This function is used to deinitialise a GPIO pin. It should be called if the primary function of the pin is to be restored or in the event of a system shutdown. This function can be called in the interrupt context.

The pins register settings will be restored to their default values. The pin will be deselected as a GPIO pin.

Parameters:
*psPin Pointer to initialised pin descriptor.
Returns:
This function returns as follows:
GPIO_STATUS_OK Operation completed successfully.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_UNINITIALISED GPIO has not been intialised.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_INACTIVE Pin descriptor is inactive.

GPIO_STATUS_T GPIODeinit (  ) 

Description:
This function is used to deinitialise the GPIO API. This function should not be called in the interrupt context.

Returns:
This function returns as follows:
GPIO_STATUS_OK Operation completed successfully.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_UNINITIALISED GPIO has not been intialised.
GPIO_STATUS_ERR_ACTIVEPINS There are active pins that must be removed using GPIORemovePin.
